13/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police in Belgrade announced on Thursday (August 12th) the arrest one of the suspects in an attack against two German citizens earlier in the day. One of the victims, a 25-year-old man, was seriously injured after he was stabbed in the back. The other man sustained minor injuries. Police say the attackers stole the victims' mobile phones and wallets. (Radio Free Europe, B92 - 12/08/10)
